race.comment: NIC THE CASH (2) has a second placing to Ahha Ahha to his name, which looks good form for this. Spelled after that run and after an adequate fresh run he got back into the placings last start and is ready for this longer trip now. KADDARI (9) has got into the placings in better races than this in the past and while she will be at her best over further, her jumpouts suggest a forward showing would not shock. THE QUIET IMMORTAL (6) is another who's trialled well and resumes on the home track, where he's likely to appreciate firmer ground than he struck on debut. TALLINGAS INDIROSE (14) almost pulled off a massive upset in a handy maiden at Wodonga on Cup Day and has a fitness edge on a number of the key chances here. SPARKLES (13) was a massive drifter on debut and ran accordingly but is in a new camp now and surged away late under light riding for a recent Bendigo jumpout win.
